# MONOS — Status Badge Rule (v1)

Use **one shared QSS badge style** and switch colors via a **dynamic property** (`status`) on a single `QLabel`.

## QSS (Style Sheet)

```css
/* Base badge */
QLabel#StatusBadge {
  font-family: "Inter";
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: bold;
  padding: 2px 8px;
  border-radius: 4px;
  border: 1px solid transparent;
  /* Qt Widgets: simulate glass with rgba */
  background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 100); /* prefer higher alpha for readability over thumbnails */
}

QLabel#StatusBadge[status="ready"] {
  color: #10b981;
  background-color: rgba(16, 185, 129, 100);
  border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 50);
}
QLabel#StatusBadge[status="progress"] {
  color: #3b82f6;
  background-color: rgba(59, 130, 246, 100);
  border: 1px solid rgba(59, 130, 246, 50);
}
QLabel#StatusBadge[status="blocked"] {
  color: #ef4444;
  background-color: rgba(239, 68, 68, 100);
  border: 1px solid rgba(239, 68, 68, 50);
}
QLabel#StatusBadge[status="waiting"] {
  color: #71717a;
  background-color: rgba(113, 113, 122, 100);
  border: 1px solid rgba(113, 113, 122, 50);
}
```

## Python usage (Qt Widgets)

```python
badge = QLabel(parent)
badge.setObjectName("StatusBadge")

# QSS can't do uppercase/tracking reliably
badge.setText(status_text.upper())
f = badge.font()
f.setLetterSpacing(QFont.PercentageSpacing, 95)  # tracking-tighter
badge.setFont(f)

badge.setProperty("status", status_key)  # "ready"|"progress"|"blocked"|"waiting"
badge.style().unpolish(badge)
badge.style().polish(badge)
```

## Notes

- Qt Widgets does **not** support true backdrop-blur over pixmaps; use rgba with higher alpha instead.
- Keep this **read-only**: no dropdown/select in the Inspector by default.
